{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "82-pair evaluation set for the deterministic NL → ES|QL translator (Milestone 5B). Each entry is a natural-language security question plus the structured intents we expect the parser to extract. We score on (a) syntactic validity of the emitted ES|QL (parsed by services/agents/app/nl_query/grammar.py) and (b) semantic match of the parsed intents against the gold IR. The 2026-06-28 expansion (Phase 4.6) added 32 cases covering: geo-by-country-name (`from iran`, `from china`, …), quoted-string LIKE filters against `message`, MIN/MAX numeric aggregations, multi-axis group-bys (host+user, ip+port, user+country), and longer-tail SOC hosts (`db01`, `app-prod-03`, `edge1.corp.local`).",
  "index_pattern_default": "logs-*",
  "time_range_hours_default": 24,
